# Mobile phone frame (required)

Whenever you create, fix, or redesign **customer-facing, auth-entry, or admin UI**, it must render inside the phone mockup — never as a full-bleed desktop page (`dashboard-shell`).

## Required shell

```tsx
<div className="device">
  <div className="app-shell">
    {/* screen content */}
    <StatusBar />
  </div>
</div>
```

Reference implementations:
- Customer app: `src/app/(customer)/layout.tsx` (already wraps all customer routes)
- Admin portal: `src/app/admin/layout.tsx` (phone frame + bottom tab bar)
- Auth entry: `src/app/welcome/page.tsx`, `src/app/signin/page.tsx`, `src/app/login/page.tsx`

## Rules

- **New customer pages** under `src/app/(customer)/` inherit the frame from the layout — do not add a second `.device` wrapper.
- **Admin pages** under `src/app/admin/` inherit the frame from the admin layout — do not add a second `.device` wrapper or use `dashboard-shell`.
- **New auth/entry routes** outside `(customer)` (e.g. `/signin`, `/welcome`, `/login`) must wrap themselves in `.device` + `.app-shell` + `<StatusBar />`, matching `/welcome`.
- Prefer the **onboarding OTP layout** (`OtpLogin variant="onboarding"`) for customer auth screens so they fill the phone like `/welcome`.
- Do **not** use `dashboard-shell`, centered max-width cards, or desktop-only layouts for customer/auth/admin screens.
- On desktop (≥480px) `.device` is the iPhone frame; on a real phone it is `display: contents` (full viewport). Design for the 402×874 screen.

## Exceptions (no phone frame)

- Operator portals still on desktop shell: `/vendor`, `/driver`
- Build tracker: `/build`
- These correctly use `dashboard-shell`.

## Checklist before finishing UI work

1. Does the screen appear inside the phone frame on desktop?
2. If the route is outside `(customer)`, did you add `.device` / `.app-shell` / `StatusBar` (or inherit from admin layout)?
3. Did you avoid `dashboard-shell` for customer/auth/admin UI?
